elementSpec.desc:
In this document (and in all others in the SIL collection) the 'seg' element is used to encapsulate:


i) the entire sentences from original document (first level);

ii) the individual lexical items contained within the sentences (second level);

Within the sentence level "seg" (segment) elements all punctuation characters (".", ";", ":", "¿", "?", "!", etc.) are encapsulated in the "c" (character) element;
                        In future stages of the project, each of these punctuation characters will be formally linked with the linguistic categories with which it is associated: a sentence that begins with: "¿"
                           (and ends with: "?") can be immediately recognized as sentence type "question/interrogative";
